Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak met here with Syrian President Hafez Assad to try to defuse growing tension between Syria and Turkey.
The talks in Damascus came as Turkey has massed forces near the border with Syria after threatening to eradicate Kurdish rebel bases in the neighboring country.
As Turkey kept up warlike rhetoric against Damascus, Egypt began shuttle democracy between the two neighbors to avoid a military confrontation over Turkish Kurdish bases in Syria.
